sentences: Francisca Viveros Barradas, (born April 2, 1947) known professionally as Paquita
Paquita started her career in Mexico City in 1970.
Her big break came in 1986, where she performed in a Televisa show that exposed her to a bigger audience and led to a recording contract with CBS.
In the 2021 Billboard Music Awards, when Bad Bunny went to the stage to help her with mic, she told him Eres un inutil.
She was honored with the Trajectory Award at the Premio lo Nuestro awards (2016).
She also received the Lifetime Achievement Award at the 2021 Billboard Latin Music AwardsPaquita la del Barrio has inspired a television series on Univision.
Her album Romeo Y Su Nieta earned her a nomination for the 56th Annual Grammy Awards (2013) under Best Regional Mexican Music Album (Including Tejano).
Her second marriage lasted 31 years, and ended with her husband's death in 2000.
She performed at a local restaurant in Colonia Guerrero, where fans returned every week to listen to her music.
In an interview with The Miami Herald Paquita said, "I am defending women.
When she was fifteen years old she eloped with forty-four year old Miguel Magaña.
Her marriage with Magaña lasted seven years and she had two sons.
Her second marriage lasted 31 years, and ended with her husband's death in 2000.
